	<titles>
		<title type="short" as="introduced">Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation Pilots Equitable Treatment Act</title>
		<title type="official" as="introduced">To amend title IV of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 to require the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation, in the case of airline pilots who are required by regulation to retire at age 60, to compute the actuarial value of monthly benefits in the form of a life annuity commencing at age 60.</title>
